WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.840 --> 00:00:03.250
[rain falling]

2
00:00:03.340 --> 00:00:05.670
[thunder rumbling]

3
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:08.680
[breathing heavily]

4
00:00:08.760 --> 00:00:10.826
[Mike] Is there a number we can call
for your parents?

5
00:00:10.850 --> 00:00:12.930
Where's your hair?
Do you have cancer?

6
00:00:13.010 --> 00:00:14.220
[Lucas] Did you run away?

7
00:00:14.310 --> 00:00:16.310
- Are you in some kind of trouble?
- Is that blood?

8
00:00:17.020 --> 00:00:19.166
- Stop it! You're freaking her out!
- She's freaking me out!

9
00:00:19.190 --> 00:00:20.400
I bet she's deaf.

10
00:00:22.480 --> 00:00:23.570
Not deaf.

11
00:00:23.650 --> 00:00:26.950
All right. that's enough. all right?
She's just scared and cold.

12
00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:31.910
[thunder rumbles]

13
00:00:33.580 --> 00:00:35.410
Here. these are clean.
Okay?

14
00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.074
Free Gift Cards and Tech Items with
Southwest Points: www.fairylandshop.me

15
00:00:46.130 --> 00:00:47.410
- No. no. no!
- [boys exclaiming]

16
00:00:47.470 --> 00:00:49.090
[Dustin] Oh. my God.
Oh. my God.

17
00:00:49.180 --> 00:00:52.430
See over there?
[stammers] That's the bathroom.

18
00:00:52.510 --> 00:00:54.510
Privacy.
Get it?

19
00:01:09.740 --> 00:01:10.910
You don't want it closed?

20
00:01:12.740 --> 00:01:13.740
No.

21
00:01:13.830 --> 00:01:15.910
Oh. so you can speak.

22
00:01:15.990 --> 00:01:18.200
Okay. well...

23
00:01:18.290 --> 00:01:22.290
Um. how about we just keep the door...

24
00:01:24.540 --> 00:01:26.130
just like this.

25
00:01:26.630 --> 00:01:29.340
- Is that better?
- Yes.

26
00:01:34.970 --> 00:01:37.100
[Dustin] This is mental.
[Mike] At least she can talk.

27
00:01:37.180 --> 00:01:40.060
She said "no" and "yes."
Your three-year-old sister says more.

28
00:01:40.140 --> 00:01:41.850
She tried to get naked.

29
00:01:41.940 --> 00:01:43.620
There's something
seriously wrong with her.

30
00:01:43.650 --> 00:01:47.150
- Like. wrong in the head.
- She just went like...

31
00:01:47.230 --> 00:01:48.690
I bet she escaped from Pennhurst.

32
00:01:48.780 --> 00:01:51.400
- From where?
- The nuthouse in Kerley County.

33
00:01:51.490 --> 00:01:53.170
- You got a lot of family there?
- Bite me.

34
00:01:53.200 --> 00:01:55.200
Seriously though. think about it.

35
00:01:55.280 --> 00:01:58.330
That would explain her shaved hair
and why she's so crazy.

36
00:01:58.410 --> 00:01:59.570
[Dustin] Why she went like...

37
00:01:59.620 --> 00:02:02.420
She's an escapee is the point.
She's probably a psycho.

38
00:02:02.500 --> 00:02:04.500
- Like Michael Myers.
- [Lucas] Exactly!

39
00:02:04.580 --> 00:02:06.170
We should've never brought her here.

40
00:02:06.250 --> 00:02:07.646
So you just wanted to leave her
out in that storm?

41
00:02:07.670 --> 00:02:10.420
Yes! We went out to find Will.
not another problem.

42
00:02:10.510 --> 00:02:12.276
- I think we should tell your mom.
- I second that.

43
00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:14.260
- Who's crazy now?
- How is that crazy?

44
00:02:14.340 --> 00:02:16.930
'Cause. we weren't supposed to be
out tonight. remember?

45
00:02:17.010 --> 00:02:19.350
- So?
- So if I tell my mom

46
00:02:19.430 --> 00:02:21.270
and she tells your mom
and your mom...

47
00:02:21.350 --> 00:02:23.600
- Oh. man.
- Our houses become Alcatraz.

48
00:02:23.690 --> 00:02:26.270
Exactly.
We'll never find Will.

49
00:02:28.020 --> 00:02:30.570
All right. here's the plan.
She sleeps here tonight.

50
00:02:30.650 --> 00:02:32.780
- You're letting a girl...
- Just listen!

51
00:02:32.860 --> 00:02:34.820
In the morning.
she sneaks around my house.

52
00:02:34.910 --> 00:02:36.950
goes to the front door
and rings my doorbell.

53
00:02:37.030 --> 00:02:38.870
My mom will answer and know
exactly what to do.

54
00:02:38.910 --> 00:02:41.226
She'll send her back to Pennhurst
or wherever she comes from.

55
00:02:41.250 --> 00:02:42.436
We'll be totally in the clear.

56
00:02:42.460 --> 00:02:44.250
And tomorrow night. we go back out.

57
00:02:44.330 --> 00:02:46.710
And this time. we find Will.

58
00:02:51.340 --> 00:02:53.340
Here you go.
This is my sleeping bag.

59
00:02:53.420 --> 00:02:55.720
[Dustin] You really think she's psycho?

60
00:02:55.800 --> 00:02:57.390
Wouldn't want her in my house.

61
00:03:01.810 --> 00:03:03.430
[sighs] Mental.

62
00:03:05.600 --> 00:03:07.770
Hey. um. I never asked your name.

63
00:03:07.860 --> 00:03:09.110
[door closes]

64
00:03:15.240 --> 00:03:16.490
Is that real?

65
00:03:19.330 --> 00:03:23.580
Sorry. I've just... never seen
a kid with a tattoo before.

66
00:03:24.410 --> 00:03:26.210
What's it mean?
Eleven?

67
00:03:29.540 --> 00:03:30.670
That's your name?

68
00:03:32.800 --> 00:03:34.840
Eleven. Okay.

69
00:03:34.920 --> 00:03:38.260
Um. well. my name's Mike.
Short for Michael.

70
00:03:38.340 --> 00:03:41.560
Maybe we can call you "El."
Short for Eleven.

71
00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:47.020
Um. well. okay.

72
00:03:47.940 --> 00:03:49.190
'Night. El.

73
00:03:51.440 --> 00:03:52.730
'Night. Mike.

74
00:04:10.170 --> 00:04:12.000
[door opens and closes]

75
00:04:17.130 --> 00:04:18.890
[thunder rumbling]

76
00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:33.520
[theme music playing]

77
00:05:47.140 --> 00:05:50.810
All right. Mom.
Breakfast is ready.

78
00:05:50.890 --> 00:05:53.690
- What? No. be careful of the poster.
- Yeah. okay. All right.

79
00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:55.650
- I can't eat.
- I just need you to eat. Mom.

80
00:05:55.730 --> 00:05:59.150
[sniffles] Listen. Listen. the Xerox place
opens in. like. 30 minutes.

81
00:05:59.240 --> 00:06:00.716
- Yeah.
- And I don't want you to go alone...

82
00:06:00.740 --> 00:06:01.876
No. I know.
I told you. I got it.

83
00:06:01.900 --> 00:06:04.320
...so I'm gonna have Karen take you.
'cause I should be here.

84
00:06:04.410 --> 00:06:06.780
- Okay.
- We need to make. what. 200. 300 copies?

85
00:06:06.870 --> 00:06:08.056
- How much is a copy?
- Yeah. okay.

86
00:06:08.080 --> 00:06:09.226
- Okay. Mom. Mom.
- Ten cents?

87
00:06:09.250 --> 00:06:11.870
- [stammering] If we... Ten cents...
- Mom. Mom. Mom!

88
00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:14.210
[stutters] You can't get like this. okay?

89
00:06:14.290 --> 00:06:16.710
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- No. it's okay.

90
00:06:16.790 --> 00:06:18.340
[knocking on door]

91
00:06:19.300 --> 00:06:22.590
[sighs] We've been waiting six hours.

92
00:06:22.680 --> 00:06:24.390
I know.
I came as soon as I could.

93
00:06:24.470 --> 00:06:26.050
Six hours.

94
00:06:26.140 --> 00:06:28.260
A little bit of trust here. all right?

95
00:06:28.350 --> 00:06:31.310
We've been searching all night.
Went all the way to Cartersville.

96
00:06:31.390 --> 00:06:33.060
- And?
- Nothing.

97
00:06:33.140 --> 00:06:34.560
God.

98
00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:38.650
Flo says you got a phone call?

99
00:06:38.730 --> 00:06:40.900
Oh. yeah.

100
00:06:42.400 --> 00:06:43.610
[Joyce sniffles]

101
00:06:48.200 --> 00:06:49.880
[Hopper] Storm barbecued this pretty good.

102
00:06:49.910 --> 00:06:52.330
- The storm?
- What else?

103
00:06:52.410 --> 00:06:55.330
You're saying that that's not weird?

104
00:06:55.420 --> 00:06:57.080
No. it's weird.

105
00:06:57.170 --> 00:06:59.670
Can we. like. trace who made the call?
Contact the...

106
00:06:59.750 --> 00:07:01.760
No. it doesn't work like that.

107
00:07:01.840 --> 00:07:03.590
Now. uh. you're sure it was Will?

108
00:07:03.670 --> 00:07:05.406
Because Flo said
you just heard some breathing.

109
00:07:05.430 --> 00:07:08.470
No. It was him.
It was Will.

110
00:07:09.470 --> 00:07:13.520
[voice breaking] And he was scared.
And then something...

111
00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:16.440
It was probably just a prank call.
It was somebody trying to scare you.

112
00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:18.336
- Who would do that?
- Well. this thing's been on TV.

113
00:07:18.360 --> 00:07:21.530
It brings out all the crazies. you know.
False leads. prank calls. uh...

114
00:07:21.610 --> 00:07:24.610
No. Hopper. it was not a prank.
It was him.

115
00:07:24.700 --> 00:07:27.320
- Joyce.
- Come on. how about a little trust here?

116
00:07:28.320 --> 00:07:30.620
What. you think I'm... I'm making this up?

117
00:07:30.700 --> 00:07:32.216
I'm not saying that you're making it up.

118
00:07:32.240 --> 00:07:34.710
All I'm saying is
it's an emotional time for you.

119
00:07:34.790 --> 00:07:38.080
And you think I don't know
my own son's breathing?

120
00:07:38.170 --> 00:07:39.790
Wouldn't you know your own daughter's?

121
00:07:51.100 --> 00:07:52.100
[Joyce sniffles]

122
00:07:53.680 --> 00:07:56.850
- You hear from. uh. Lonnie yet?
- No.

123
00:07:57.440 --> 00:07:59.376
It's been long enough.
I'm having him checked out.

124
00:07:59.400 --> 00:08:01.070
[Joyce sighs] Oh. come on!

125
00:08:01.150 --> 00:08:03.230
You're wasting your time.

126
00:08:05.190 --> 00:08:06.950
Hey. Hopper.

127
00:08:07.030 --> 00:08:09.200
Hopper. [panting]

128
00:08:09.280 --> 00:08:10.530
Let me go.

129
00:08:12.160 --> 00:08:13.950
- I'm sorry?
- To Lonnie's.

130
00:08:14.040 --> 00:08:16.910
[stammering] You know. if Will's there.
it means he ran away.

131
00:08:17.000 --> 00:08:19.420
And if he sees the cops.
he'll think he's in trouble.

132
00:08:19.500 --> 00:08:21.210
He'll... He'll hide.

133
00:08:21.290 --> 00:08:23.000
- You know. he's good at hiding.
- Yeah?

134
00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:26.420
Well. cops are good at finding.
Okay?

135
00:08:26.510 --> 00:08:28.180
Stay here with your mom.

136
00:08:29.390 --> 00:08:30.470
She needs you.

137
00:08:35.140 --> 00:08:36.560
[engine starting]

138
00:08:37.940 --> 00:08:39.480
[music playing faintly on TV]

139
00:08:49.200 --> 00:08:51.820
Slow down. Mike.
That's disgusting.

140
00:08:53.280 --> 00:08:55.160
Do a lot of studying last night?

141
00:08:55.910 --> 00:08:57.830
Yeah. actually. I did.

142
00:08:57.910 --> 00:09:00.290
What was your test on again?
Human anatomy?

143
00:09:02.330 --> 00:09:04.090
Hey. what's going on?

144
00:09:05.380 --> 00:09:06.590
[both] Nothing.

145
00:09:09.300 --> 00:09:10.800
[radio static]

146
00:09:10.890 --> 00:09:12.640
[footsteps approaching]

147
00:09:18.020 --> 00:09:19.390
Hey. you found my supercomm.

148
00:09:19.480 --> 00:09:20.640
Pretty cool. huh?

149
00:09:21.310 --> 00:09:22.610
I talk to my friends with it.

150
00:09:22.690 --> 00:09:24.570
Mostly Lucas.
'cause he lives so close.

151
00:09:24.650 --> 00:09:25.730
Signal's pretty weak.

152
00:09:29.950 --> 00:09:31.110
Got you breakfast.

153
00:09:33.700 --> 00:09:35.660
So listen. this is gonna
sound a little weird.

154
00:09:35.740 --> 00:09:37.136
but I just need you to go out there.

155
00:09:37.160 --> 00:09:39.290
Then go to the front door
and ring the doorbell.

156
00:09:39.370 --> 00:09:42.920
My mom will answer and you'll tell her
that you're lost and that you need help.

157
00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:47.130
But whatever you do. you can't tell her
about last night or that you know me.

158
00:09:47.210 --> 00:09:48.210
Understand?

159
00:09:49.340 --> 00:09:50.720
Really. it's no big deal.

160
00:09:50.800 --> 00:09:52.930
We'll just pretend
to meet each other again.

161
00:09:53.930 --> 00:09:56.600
And my mom. she'll know who to call.

162
00:09:59.060 --> 00:10:00.100
No.

163
00:10:01.390 --> 00:10:02.520
No?

164
00:10:03.350 --> 00:10:04.360
No.

165
00:10:05.360 --> 00:10:08.780
No... you don't want my mom to get help?

166
00:10:13.570 --> 00:10:16.120
You're in trouble. aren't you?

167
00:10:19.950 --> 00:10:21.000
Who...

168
00:10:22.460 --> 00:10:24.130
Who are you in trouble with?

169
00:10:26.880 --> 00:10:28.420
Bad.

170
00:10:28.500 --> 00:10:29.590
Bad?

171
00:10:30.590 --> 00:10:31.760
Bad people?

172
00:10:35.430 --> 00:10:37.470
They want to hurt you?

173
00:10:37.560 --> 00:10:38.970
The bad people?

174
00:10:48.730 --> 00:10:50.400
Understand?

175
00:10:51.490 --> 00:10:53.990
[Karen] Michael. where are you?
We're going to be late.

176
00:10:54.070 --> 00:10:55.846
- Let's go!
- [stammers] All right. I'll be back.

177
00:10:55.870 --> 00:10:57.620
Just stay here. okay?
Stay here.

178
00:10:58.700 --> 00:11:00.370
[footsteps receding]

179
00:11:04.960 --> 00:11:06.380
When was this?

180
00:11:06.460 --> 00:11:08.090
Last night.
Less than two miles away.

181
00:11:08.170 --> 00:11:09.960
- And the boy?
- Still missing.

182
00:11:10.710 --> 00:11:13.760
[Joyce] <i>It was my son.</i>
<i>I know it.</i>

183
00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:16.140
<i>And I... I heard something else.</i>

184
00:11:16.220 --> 00:11:17.600
[Florence] <i>Something else?</i>

185
00:11:18.800 --> 00:11:22.310
[Joyce] <i>It was like. uh.</i>
<i>some kind of animal.</i>

186
00:11:22.390 --> 00:11:25.900
[stammers] <i>I don't know.</i>
<i>Just please tell Hop to hurry.</i>

187
00:11:25.980 --> 00:11:28.900
[volunteers shouting] Will! Will Byers!

188
00:11:29.770 --> 00:11:31.650
[Callahan] Will Byers!

189
00:11:31.730 --> 00:11:33.240
[dog barking]

190
00:11:34.190 --> 00:11:36.490
[Powell] Will!
[volunteers] Will!

191
00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:39.330
[Hopper] Hey!
Anything?

192
00:11:40.280 --> 00:11:41.330
[Callahan] You?

193
00:11:42.290 --> 00:11:44.540
[Hopper] No. nothing but a dead phone.

194
00:11:44.620 --> 00:11:45.620
[Callahan] Joyce?

195
00:11:45.710 --> 00:11:48.460
About one step from falling off the edge.

196
00:11:48.540 --> 00:11:50.960
She's been a few steps
for a while now. hasn't she?

197
00:11:51.050 --> 00:11:52.800
Kid's missing. man.

198
00:11:52.880 --> 00:11:54.170
Show a little class.

199
00:11:55.170 --> 00:11:57.680
All right. Come on. let's go!

200
00:11:57.760 --> 00:12:00.010
We got a lot of ground to cover.

201
00:12:00.100 --> 00:12:02.510
The chief and her.
they've screwed before. huh?

202
00:12:05.060 --> 00:12:06.730
Will!

203
00:12:06.810 --> 00:12:08.270
That a "yeah" or did they...

204
00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:11.400
- Will!
- Will!

205
00:12:18.950 --> 00:12:22.370
"When alpha particles go through
gold foil. they become..."

206
00:12:22.450 --> 00:12:25.000
- Unoccupied space.
- "A molecule that can..."

207
00:12:25.080 --> 00:12:26.226
- Hey!
- [Steve] I don't know.

208
00:12:26.250 --> 00:12:27.596
I think you've studied enough. Nance.

209
00:12:27.620 --> 00:12:29.726
- [Nancy] Steve...
- I'm telling you. you know. you got this.

210
00:12:29.750 --> 00:12:32.090
Don't worry.
Now. on to more important matters.

211
00:12:32.170 --> 00:12:35.130
My dad has left town on a conference
and my mom's gone with him.

212
00:12:35.210 --> 00:12:37.630
- 'cause. you know. she doesn't trust him.
- Good call.

213
00:12:37.720 --> 00:12:38.720
So are you in?

214
00:12:38.800 --> 00:12:40.220
In for what?

215
00:12:40.300 --> 00:12:42.050
No parents? Big house?

216
00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:43.850
A party?

217
00:12:43.930 --> 00:12:45.850
- [Carol] Ding. ding. ding!
- [Tommy laughs]

218
00:12:45.980 --> 00:12:47.390
It's Tuesday.

219
00:12:47.480 --> 00:12:48.940
[mocking] It's Tuesday!
Oh. my God.

220
00:12:49.020 --> 00:12:50.350
- [both laughing]
- Come on.

221
00:12:50.440 --> 00:12:52.190
It'll be low key.
It'll just be us.

222
00:12:52.270 --> 00:12:54.650
What do you say?
Are you in or are you out?

223
00:12:54.730 --> 00:12:58.570
- Um...
- Oh. God. Look.

224
00:12:59.570 --> 00:13:01.280
Oh. God. that's depressing.

225
00:13:03.490 --> 00:13:06.750
- Should we say something?
- I don't think he speaks.

226
00:13:06.830 --> 00:13:08.580
How much you want to bet he killed him?

227
00:13:08.660 --> 00:13:09.920
Shut up.

228
00:13:17.210 --> 00:13:18.720
[Nancy] Hey.

229
00:13:18.800 --> 00:13:20.380
Oh. hey.

230
00:13:20.470 --> 00:13:21.640
I just...

231
00:13:22.800 --> 00:13:26.100
I wanted to say. you know. um...

232
00:13:26.180 --> 00:13:28.100
I'm sorry about everything.

233
00:13:33.520 --> 00:13:35.820
Everyone's thinking about you.

234
00:13:37.940 --> 00:13:40.610
- It sucks.
- Yeah.

235
00:13:44.120 --> 00:13:45.370
I'm sure he's fine.

236
00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:47.120
He's a smart kid.

237
00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:49.000
[school bell ringing]

238
00:13:50.040 --> 00:13:51.920
I have to go.
[chuckles] Chemistry test.

239
00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:53.000
Yeah.

240
00:13:53.080 --> 00:13:54.540
- Good luck.
- Thanks.

241
00:13:59.340 --> 00:14:01.880
[principal on PA]
<i>Attention. faculty and students.</i>

242
00:14:01.970 --> 00:14:05.430
<i>At 8:00 p.m. tonight. there will be
an assembly on the football field</i>

243
00:14:05.510 --> 00:14:07.850
<i>in support of Will Byers and his family.</i>

244
00:14:07.930 --> 00:14:10.060
<i>All are encouraged to attend.</i>

245
00:14:10.140 --> 00:14:14.310
<i>Volunteer sign-ups for search parties
are still available in the office.</i>

246
00:14:16.110 --> 00:14:17.860
[indistinct chatter]

247
00:14:20.490 --> 00:14:21.700
Oh. this is weird.

248
00:14:22.150 --> 00:14:25.160
- He's never this late.
- I'm telling you. his stupid plan failed.

249
00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:26.490
I thought you liked his plan.

250
00:14:26.580 --> 00:14:28.910
Yeah. but obviously it was stupid.
or he'd be here.

251
00:14:28.990 --> 00:14:30.950
If his mom found out
a girl spent the night...

252
00:14:31.040 --> 00:14:32.540
He's in deep shit right about now.

253
00:14:32.620 --> 00:14:35.290
Hey. what if she slept naked?

254
00:14:35.380 --> 00:14:37.290
Oh. my God. she didn't.

255
00:14:37.380 --> 00:14:39.590
Oh. if Mrs. Wheeler tells my parents...

256
00:14:39.670 --> 00:14:42.550
- No way. Mike would never rat us out.
- I don't know.

257
00:14:42.630 --> 00:14:45.840
All that matters is. after school.
the freak will be back in the loony bin.

258
00:14:45.930 --> 00:14:49.060
and we can focus on what really matters.
finding Will.

259
00:15:05.200 --> 00:15:06.466
[Mike] <i>You want anything to drink?</i>

260
00:15:06.490 --> 00:15:09.160
We have OJ. skim milk...
What else?

261
00:15:10.490 --> 00:15:11.870
Um. we have...

262
00:15:13.790 --> 00:15:15.540
Oh. this is my living room.

263
00:15:15.620 --> 00:15:17.170
It's mostly just for watching TV.

264
00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:19.800
Nice. right?
It's a 22-inch.

265
00:15:19.880 --> 00:15:21.960
That's. like. ten times bigger
than Dustin's.

266
00:15:33.430 --> 00:15:35.690
- Pretty.
- I guess.

267
00:15:35.770 --> 00:15:37.190
That's my sister Nancy.

268
00:15:37.270 --> 00:15:38.900
And that's baby Holly.

269
00:15:38.980 --> 00:15:40.360
And those are my parents.

270
00:15:41.020 --> 00:15:42.150
What are your parents like?

271
00:15:42.780 --> 00:15:44.190
Do they live close?

272
00:15:46.610 --> 00:15:48.200
That's our La-Z-Boy.

273
00:15:49.910 --> 00:15:51.160
It's where my dad sleeps.

274
00:15:51.240 --> 00:15:53.950
You can try it if you want.

275
00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:55.620
Yeah.

276
00:15:56.960 --> 00:15:57.960
It's fun.

277
00:16:01.590 --> 00:16:03.420
Just trust me. okay?

278
00:16:07.510 --> 00:16:09.236
- [Mike chuckles]
- [Eleven laughs nervously]

279
00:16:09.260 --> 00:16:10.930
See? Fun. right?

280
00:16:12.810 --> 00:16:13.810
Now you try.

281
00:16:19.100 --> 00:16:20.400
[both laugh]

282
00:16:23.900 --> 00:16:25.900
[rock music playing on car stereo]

283
00:16:33.370 --> 00:16:35.370
["Should I Stay or Should I Go"
playing on stereo]

284
00:16:46.840 --> 00:16:48.380
[song continues playing on stereo]

285
00:16:48.470 --> 00:16:51.220
<i>♪ Darling. you got to let me know ♪</i>

286
00:16:52.760 --> 00:16:56.480
<i>♪ Should I stay or should I go? ♪</i>

287
00:16:56.560 --> 00:16:58.190
- You like it?
- Yeah. it's cool.

288
00:16:58.270 --> 00:16:59.990
All right. you can keep
the mix if you want.

289
00:17:00.020 --> 00:17:01.150
- Really?
- Yeah. really.

290
00:17:01.230 --> 00:17:02.810
All the best stuff's on there.

291
00:17:02.900 --> 00:17:05.820
Joy Division. Bowie. Television.
The Smiths...

292
00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:07.610
It'll totally change your life.

293
00:17:07.690 --> 00:17:09.360
Yeah. totally.

294
00:17:09.450 --> 00:17:11.530
[Joyce faintly]
Where the hell are you. Lonnie?

295
00:17:11.620 --> 00:17:13.136
I don't want to hear it.
I don't want to hear it.

296
00:17:13.160 --> 00:17:15.450
[Joyce muttering indistinctly]

297
00:17:17.830 --> 00:17:21.920
[Joyce] This is ridiculous!
I'm so sick of your excuses.

298
00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:24.800
<i>♪ One day is fine and next is black ♪</i>

299
00:17:24.880 --> 00:17:26.560
- [lowers volume]
- He's not coming. is he?

300
00:17:28.090 --> 00:17:29.470
Do you even like baseball?

301
00:17:30.590 --> 00:17:32.800
No. but... I don't know.

302
00:17:32.890 --> 00:17:34.890
- It's fun to go with him sometimes.
- Come on.

303
00:17:34.970 --> 00:17:37.720
Has he ever done anything with you
that you actually like?

304
00:17:37.810 --> 00:17:39.560
You know. like the arcade or something?

305
00:17:40.350 --> 00:17:43.060
- I don't know.
- No. all right? He hasn't.

306
00:17:43.150 --> 00:17:44.990
He's trying to force you
to like normal things.

307
00:17:45.070 --> 00:17:48.110
And you shouldn't like things because
people tell you you're supposed to.

308
00:17:48.190 --> 00:17:49.490
Okay?

309
00:17:50.280 --> 00:17:51.990
Especially not him.

310
00:17:53.870 --> 00:17:56.240
But you like The Clash? For real?

311
00:17:56.330 --> 00:17:58.450
For real.
Definitely.

312
00:17:59.200 --> 00:18:00.750
[raises volume]

313
00:18:00.830 --> 00:18:03.580
<i>♪ Should I cool it or should I blow? ♪</i>

314
00:18:05.210 --> 00:18:09.590
<i>♪ So you gotta let me know ♪</i>

315
00:18:09.670 --> 00:18:11.550
<i>♪ Should I stay or should I go? ♪</i>

316
00:18:15.930 --> 00:18:18.220
[bell tolling]

317
00:18:29.480 --> 00:18:31.490
[Christmas carol playing]

318
00:18:32.780 --> 00:18:34.200
[bells chiming]

319
00:18:35.780 --> 00:18:38.200
[Donald] Joyce. I wasn't
expecting you today.

320
00:18:38.290 --> 00:18:41.410
- I brought Jeffrey in to cover.
- [stammers] I'm not here to work.

321
00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:42.910
I... [sighs]

322
00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:45.130
The storm last night. I...

323
00:18:45.750 --> 00:18:47.920
[sighs] I need a new phone.

324
00:18:48.000 --> 00:18:49.050
[cash register dings]

325
00:18:49.130 --> 00:18:52.550
Okay. that looks like $22.56.

326
00:18:52.630 --> 00:18:54.430
Uh. yeah. you know. uh...

327
00:18:54.510 --> 00:18:56.800
I gave Jonathan all my money for...

328
00:18:56.890 --> 00:18:58.680
for the copies for the posters.

329
00:18:59.680 --> 00:19:02.140
Uh. I need an advance.

330
00:19:03.060 --> 00:19:04.560
Yes. well. of course.

331
00:19:04.650 --> 00:19:06.230
- Of course.
- [softly] Thank you.

332
00:19:08.150 --> 00:19:09.270
[Joyce sighs]

333
00:19:11.150 --> 00:19:13.650
[stammers] Yeah. uh. I was thinking.
two weeks?

334
00:19:15.910 --> 00:19:17.160
Um...

335
00:19:18.950 --> 00:19:22.290
Yes. I understand. but. you know.
I have to pay Jeffrey for covering...

336
00:19:22.370 --> 00:19:23.370
Donald.

337
00:19:23.460 --> 00:19:26.670
I've been here ten years. right?

338
00:19:26.750 --> 00:19:30.710
Have I ever called in sick
or missed a shift once?

339
00:19:30.800 --> 00:19:34.170
I've worked. uh.
Christmas Eve and Thanksgiving.

340
00:19:35.630 --> 00:19:37.680
[voice breaking] I don't know
where my boy is.

341
00:19:37.760 --> 00:19:38.970
He's gone.

342
00:19:39.050 --> 00:19:43.100
I don't know if I'm...
gonna ever see him again. if he's hurt...

343
00:19:44.850 --> 00:19:46.190
[sighs] I. uh...

344
00:19:47.730 --> 00:19:51.440
I need this phone
and two weeks' advance.

345
00:19:55.070 --> 00:19:56.820
And a pack of Camels.

346
00:20:07.170 --> 00:20:09.130
- We're all clear.
- [man] <i>Copy that.</i>

347
00:20:26.560 --> 00:20:28.060
[devices beeping]

348
00:20:49.750 --> 00:20:51.460
[beeping continues]

349
00:20:55.710 --> 00:20:57.920
- [beeping rapidly]
- [oozing]

350
00:21:06.480 --> 00:21:08.100
Extraordinary.

351
00:21:10.400 --> 00:21:11.400
[Mike grunts]

352
00:21:11.480 --> 00:21:13.940
[mimicking Yoda] Ready are you?
What knows you of ready?

353
00:21:14.020 --> 00:21:15.376
[in normal voice] His name's Yoda.

354
00:21:15.400 --> 00:21:18.530
He can use the Force to move things
with his mind. like this.

355
00:21:18.610 --> 00:21:19.950
Whoosh!

356
00:21:21.700 --> 00:21:23.410
Oh. this is my dinosaur. Rory.

357
00:21:23.490 --> 00:21:25.386
Look. he has a speaker in his mouth
so he can roar.

358
00:21:25.410 --> 00:21:27.540
[Rory roaring]

359
00:21:34.090 --> 00:21:36.380
Oh. these are all my
science fair trophies.

360
00:21:36.460 --> 00:21:38.800
We got first every year.

361
00:21:38.880 --> 00:21:41.590
Except for last year when we got third.

362
00:21:41.680 --> 00:21:43.760
Mr. Clarke said it was totally political.

363
00:22:03.740 --> 00:22:04.870
You know Will?

364
00:22:05.910 --> 00:22:10.040
Did you see him? Last night?
On the road?

365
00:22:11.120 --> 00:22:12.750
[vehicle approaching]

366
00:22:16.550 --> 00:22:17.710
We gotta go.

367
00:22:21.260 --> 00:22:23.300
[Karen] I bought pizza
and macaroni.

368
00:22:23.390 --> 00:22:24.930
[Holly] Okay.
[Karen] Okay.

369
00:22:28.430 --> 00:22:30.560
Ted? Is that you?

370
00:22:30.640 --> 00:22:31.850
Just me. Mom!

371
00:22:31.940 --> 00:22:34.600
- Mike? What are you doing home?
- One second!

372
00:22:39.030 --> 00:22:40.940
In here.
I'll be right back. okay?

373
00:22:41.030 --> 00:22:43.740
Please. you have to get in.
or my mom. she'll find you.

374
00:22:43.820 --> 00:22:45.780
Do you understand?

375
00:22:45.870 --> 00:22:47.450
I won't tell her about you.
I promise.

376
00:22:47.530 --> 00:22:48.910
Promise?

377
00:22:48.990 --> 00:22:51.000
It means something that you can't break.

378
00:22:51.080 --> 00:22:53.000
- Ever.
- [Karen] Michael?

379
00:22:53.620 --> 00:22:54.670
Please?

380
00:22:54.750 --> 00:22:56.330
[sighs]

381
00:23:01.880 --> 00:23:03.590
[breathing heavily]

382
00:23:12.430 --> 00:23:13.730
[Eleven echoing] Pop!

383
00:23:15.730 --> 00:23:17.860
[sobbing]

384
00:23:17.940 --> 00:23:19.270
[normal] Papa!

385
00:23:20.570 --> 00:23:21.860
Papa!

386
00:23:21.940 --> 00:23:23.280
No!

387
00:23:24.200 --> 00:23:25.320
Papa!

388
00:23:25.410 --> 00:23:27.740
No! No!
No!

389
00:23:28.370 --> 00:23:29.870
[screams]

390
00:23:32.540 --> 00:23:33.580
Papa!

391
00:23:33.660 --> 00:23:35.330
- Papa!
- [banging on door]

392
00:23:35.420 --> 00:23:36.830
Papa!

393
00:23:36.920 --> 00:23:39.000
[sobbing] Papa!

394
00:23:39.090 --> 00:23:40.250
[echoing] Papa!

395
00:23:40.340 --> 00:23:41.710
[sobs]

396
00:23:43.840 --> 00:23:44.880
Papa.

397
00:23:49.890 --> 00:23:51.180
[sobbing]

398
00:23:54.480 --> 00:23:56.900
I just... I don't feel good.

399
00:23:56.980 --> 00:23:59.650
I woke up and my head.
it really hurt bad.

400
00:23:59.730 --> 00:24:01.970
and my throat was all scratchy.
and I wanted to tell you.

401
00:24:02.030 --> 00:24:03.466
but the last time I told you I was sick

402
00:24:03.490 --> 00:24:05.466
- you made me go to school anyway. and...
- Michael.

403
00:24:05.490 --> 00:24:08.320
- Yeah?
- I'm not mad at you.

404
00:24:08.410 --> 00:24:11.700
- No?
- No. of course not.

405
00:24:12.580 --> 00:24:13.950
[sighs]

406
00:24:14.040 --> 00:24:16.960
All this that's been going on with Will.

407
00:24:17.040 --> 00:24:19.170
I can't imagine
what it's been like for you.

408
00:24:20.500 --> 00:24:21.960
I just...

409
00:24:22.500 --> 00:24:24.510
I want you to feel like
you can talk to me.

410
00:24:24.590 --> 00:24:28.340
I never want you to feel like you have
to hide anything from me.

411
00:24:28.430 --> 00:24:30.550
I'm here for you. Okay?

412
00:24:31.510 --> 00:24:32.560
[thud]

413
00:24:33.140 --> 00:24:34.310
Is there someone else here?

414
00:24:36.020 --> 00:24:37.020
No.

415
00:24:39.150 --> 00:24:40.520
Eleven?

416
00:24:40.610 --> 00:24:42.190
Is everything okay?

417
00:24:42.270 --> 00:24:43.320
El?

418
00:24:47.740 --> 00:24:49.700
- [sobs] Mike.
- Is everything okay?

419
00:24:49.780 --> 00:24:50.990
[inhales]

420
00:24:52.660 --> 00:24:54.120
Are you sure?

421
00:24:55.410 --> 00:24:56.790
Promise.

422
00:25:09.550 --> 00:25:11.140
[dial tone]

423
00:25:23.570 --> 00:25:24.610
[grunts]

424
00:25:28.110 --> 00:25:29.450
[exhales]

425
00:25:32.820 --> 00:25:36.330
[volunteer 1] Will Byers!
[volunteer 2] Will!

426
00:25:38.540 --> 00:25:40.016
[Hopper] Whoa. whoa.
Careful. careful.

427
00:25:40.040 --> 00:25:42.250
I need you alive for the next few days.
at least.

428
00:25:42.330 --> 00:25:44.590
[Callahan] Oh. hell. I could survive that.

429
00:25:44.670 --> 00:25:45.670
[Hopper laughs]

430
00:25:45.750 --> 00:25:47.800
[Callahan] What?
George Burness made the jump.

431
00:25:47.880 --> 00:25:50.220
And he was drunk as a skunk.
He did it on a $10 bet.

432
00:25:50.300 --> 00:25:51.300
George is a liar.

433
00:25:51.380 --> 00:25:54.260
You make that jump from this height.
that water turns into cement.

434
00:25:54.350 --> 00:25:56.950
Hits you like a ton of bricks.
Break every damn bone in your body.

435
00:25:59.930 --> 00:26:01.140
Nah.

436
00:26:01.230 --> 00:26:03.020
[Florence on radio] <i>Chief. you copy?</i>

437
00:26:04.610 --> 00:26:06.110
Yeah. Flo. talk to me.

438
00:26:06.190 --> 00:26:08.940
<i>Hey. Chief. we got a call
from over at Benny's.</i>

439
00:26:09.030 --> 00:26:10.860
<i>I think you need to get there right away.</i>

440
00:26:15.200 --> 00:26:17.580
[indistinct radio chatter]

441
00:26:28.090 --> 00:26:29.710
[siren wailing]

442
00:26:33.800 --> 00:26:35.300
Ugh. Jesus!

443
00:26:35.390 --> 00:26:36.640
[flies buzzing]

444
00:26:41.480 --> 00:26:42.600
Suicide?

445
00:26:44.060 --> 00:26:45.560
Mmm-hmm.

446
00:26:45.650 --> 00:26:47.730
[Callahan] Missing kid. suicide...

447
00:26:47.820 --> 00:26:50.530
You must feel like a big city cop again.
huh. Chief?

448
00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:54.990
Well. I mostly dealt
with strangers back then.

449
00:26:57.450 --> 00:26:59.240
Benny was my friend.

450
00:27:07.460 --> 00:27:09.590
[music playing on car stereo]

451
00:27:30.190 --> 00:27:32.240
[music playing on TV]

452
00:27:36.030 --> 00:27:37.320
Hello?

453
00:27:37.410 --> 00:27:38.530
[banging on door]

454
00:27:38.620 --> 00:27:39.830
[Cynthia] Yeah.

455
00:27:42.950 --> 00:27:45.250
- Can I help you?
- Yeah. is Lonnie around?

456
00:27:45.330 --> 00:27:47.396
- Yeah. he's out back. What do you want?
- To look around.

457
00:27:47.420 --> 00:27:49.920
- Hey. what do you think you're doing? Hey!
- I'll be fast.

458
00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:51.340
[Jonathan] Hey. Will?

459
00:27:51.420 --> 00:27:52.800
Will!

460
00:27:52.880 --> 00:27:54.970
Will. you here?
Will!

461
00:27:58.300 --> 00:27:59.800
[grunts]

462
00:27:59.890 --> 00:28:01.100
Get off!

463
00:28:02.270 --> 00:28:03.850
Damn. you've gotten stronger.

464
00:28:03.930 --> 00:28:06.060
Will someone please explain
what the hell is going on?

465
00:28:07.020 --> 00:28:10.320
Jonathan. Cynthia.
Cynthia. this is Jonathan.

466
00:28:10.400 --> 00:28:11.400
My oldest.

467
00:28:13.480 --> 00:28:16.360
- Come here.
- Get off me. man.

468
00:28:26.040 --> 00:28:27.170
[door closes]

469
00:28:29.540 --> 00:28:31.840
- Are you out of your mind?
- Just listen to me.

470
00:28:31.920 --> 00:28:33.776
- You are out of your mind!
- She knows about Will.

471
00:28:33.800 --> 00:28:35.510
What do you mean she knows about Will?

472
00:28:36.630 --> 00:28:39.680
She pointed at him. at his picture.
She knew he was missing. I could tell.

473
00:28:39.760 --> 00:28:41.640
- [Lucas] You could tell?
- Just think about it.

474
00:28:41.720 --> 00:28:43.996
Do you really think it was a coincidence
that we found her on Mirkwood.

475
00:28:44.020 --> 00:28:45.640
the same place where Will disappeared?

476
00:28:45.730 --> 00:28:48.020
- That is weird.
- And she said bad people are after her.

477
00:28:48.100 --> 00:28:51.400
I think maybe these bad people
are the same ones that took Will.

478
00:28:51.480 --> 00:28:54.860
- I think she knows what happened to him.
- Then why doesn't she tell us?

479
00:28:57.030 --> 00:28:59.070
Do you know where he is?

480
00:28:59.160 --> 00:29:00.216
[loudly] Do you know where Will is?

481
00:29:00.240 --> 00:29:02.580
- Stop it. you're scaring her!
- She should be scared!

482
00:29:02.660 --> 00:29:05.540
If you know where he is. tell us!

483
00:29:06.870 --> 00:29:09.420
This is nuts.
We have to take her to your mom.

484
00:29:09.500 --> 00:29:11.920
No! Eleven said telling any adult
would put us in danger.

485
00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:14.420
- What kind of danger?
- Her name is Eleven?

486
00:29:14.500 --> 00:29:17.010
- El for short.
- Mike. what kind of danger?

487
00:29:17.090 --> 00:29:18.720
Danger danger.

488
00:29:24.560 --> 00:29:26.470
No. no. no!

489
00:29:26.560 --> 00:29:29.310
We're going back to plan A.
We're telling your mom.

490
00:29:40.910 --> 00:29:41.990
No.

491
00:29:48.200 --> 00:29:50.920
[Lonnie] Take a look at this beaut.
Should've seen it when I got it.

492
00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:52.880
Took me a year. but it's almost done.

493
00:29:53.880 --> 00:29:56.750
Really?
You want to check up my ass. too?

494
00:29:57.420 --> 00:29:59.260
I told you the same thing
as I told those cops.

495
00:29:59.340 --> 00:30:00.930
he's not here and he never has been.

496
00:30:01.010 --> 00:30:04.010
- Then why didn't you call Mom back?
- I don't know. I just...

497
00:30:04.100 --> 00:30:06.600
I assumed she just forgot where he was.

498
00:30:06.680 --> 00:30:08.220
You know. he was lost or something.

499
00:30:09.270 --> 00:30:11.560
That boy never was very good
at taking care of himself.

500
00:30:11.640 --> 00:30:14.770
This isn't some joke. all right?
There are search parties. reporters...

501
00:30:14.860 --> 00:30:16.190
Hopper's not still chief. is he?

502
00:30:18.320 --> 00:30:21.400
Tell your mother
she's gotta get you out of that hellhole.

503
00:30:21.490 --> 00:30:23.450
Come out here to the city.

504
00:30:23.530 --> 00:30:25.160
People are more real here. you know?

505
00:30:26.530 --> 00:30:27.950
And then I could see you more.

506
00:30:30.120 --> 00:30:32.580
- What. you think I don't want to see you?
- I know you don't.

507
00:30:32.670 --> 00:30:34.710
See. that's your mother talkin'
right there.

508
00:30:35.960 --> 00:30:37.090
She even know you're here?

509
00:30:38.130 --> 00:30:39.130
Oh. great.

510
00:30:39.210 --> 00:30:41.920
So one kid goes missing.
the other one runs wild?

511
00:30:42.010 --> 00:30:43.800
Some real fine parenting right there.

512
00:30:43.890 --> 00:30:47.640
Look. all I'm saying is.
maybe I'm not the asshole. all right?

513
00:30:52.350 --> 00:30:54.020
In case you forgot what he looks like.

514
00:30:57.610 --> 00:30:59.360
[Cynthia] He's kinda cute. hmm?

515
00:30:59.440 --> 00:31:01.490
Maybe I'll trade you in
for the younger model?

516
00:31:03.950 --> 00:31:05.630
[Earl] Just doesn't make any sense. Chief.

517
00:31:09.040 --> 00:31:10.450
You. uh. notice anything...

518
00:31:11.500 --> 00:31:12.870
odd about him the last few weeks?

519
00:31:12.960 --> 00:31:16.210
No. we're fixin' to go fishing
down the Etowah next Sunday.

520
00:31:16.290 --> 00:31:18.420
I mean. he was lookin' forward to it.
I know that.

521
00:31:18.500 --> 00:31:20.710
He got any enemies you might know about?

522
00:31:20.800 --> 00:31:22.880
I mean.
people who might not want him around?

523
00:31:22.970 --> 00:31:25.970
[sighs] The exes didn't like him much.
That's for sure. but...

524
00:31:26.970 --> 00:31:28.510
nah.

525
00:31:28.600 --> 00:31:32.350
- When was the last time you saw him?
- Yesterday. Lunch. same as always.

526
00:31:32.430 --> 00:31:34.690
- Just you and the boys?
- Yep.

527
00:31:34.770 --> 00:31:36.850
Me and Henry and... [sighs]

528
00:31:38.150 --> 00:31:40.690
Well. there was this. uh. this kid.

529
00:31:41.690 --> 00:31:42.820
No kid did this.

530
00:31:43.780 --> 00:31:44.820
Kid?

531
00:31:46.240 --> 00:31:47.700
What are you talking about?

532
00:31:47.780 --> 00:31:52.700
Yeah. At lunch. uh.
there was this boy that. uh...

533
00:31:52.790 --> 00:31:55.540
I mean. he was trying to steal
food out of Benny's kitchen.

534
00:31:55.620 --> 00:31:57.000
Can you imagine that?

535
00:31:59.960 --> 00:32:01.000
This kid...

536
00:32:02.630 --> 00:32:03.760
what'd he look like?

537
00:32:04.920 --> 00:32:08.220
Well. he was about yea high.
You know. tiny like.

538
00:32:08.300 --> 00:32:10.736
I didn't get a good look at him. though.
He was back in the kitchen.

539
00:32:10.760 --> 00:32:12.220
He look like this?

540
00:32:13.020 --> 00:32:15.940
Oh. no. that's...
That's Lonnie's missin' kid.

541
00:32:16.020 --> 00:32:18.060
No. This was a different kid.

542
00:32:18.150 --> 00:32:19.610
This one had really short hair.

543
00:32:19.690 --> 00:32:21.770
I mean. it was buzzed
nearly down to the scalp.

544
00:32:21.860 --> 00:32:24.490
Yeah. well. let's...
You know. let's forget about the haircut.

545
00:32:24.570 --> 00:32:27.660
I mean. if this kid had a buzz cut...

546
00:32:27.740 --> 00:32:29.120
could it be Lonnie's kid?

547
00:32:29.870 --> 00:32:32.160
Well. I...
I didn't get a good look at him.

548
00:32:34.160 --> 00:32:36.120
About the right height. though.

549
00:32:36.210 --> 00:32:37.870
I mean. could've been.

550
00:32:38.960 --> 00:32:40.630
Yeah. that's...

551
00:32:40.710 --> 00:32:41.710
Could've been.

552
00:32:43.630 --> 00:32:45.130
[sighs]

553
00:32:45.210 --> 00:32:47.930
Because I don't want to go by myself.

554
00:32:48.010 --> 00:32:51.180
Barb...
Barb. it's not rocket science.

555
00:32:51.260 --> 00:32:54.640
You just tell your parents you're gonna
stay at my place afterwards.

556
00:32:54.720 --> 00:32:57.600
No. tell them we're... studying.

557
00:32:57.690 --> 00:32:59.400
[Karen] Nancy! Dinner!

558
00:32:59.480 --> 00:33:01.190
Coming!

559
00:33:01.270 --> 00:33:03.940
Look. I gotta go.
I'll see you in an hour.

560
00:33:13.660 --> 00:33:15.290
Something wrong with the meatloaf?

561
00:33:16.160 --> 00:33:19.210
Oh. no. I had two
bologna sandwiches for lunch.

562
00:33:21.000 --> 00:33:22.000
I don't know why.

563
00:33:22.080 --> 00:33:23.960
[chuckles] Me. too.

564
00:33:25.170 --> 00:33:27.510
- It's delicious. Mommy.
- Thank you. sweetie.

565
00:33:28.340 --> 00:33:29.970
So. there's this...

566
00:33:30.050 --> 00:33:32.550
special assembly thing tonight...

567
00:33:32.640 --> 00:33:34.930
for Will at the school field.

568
00:33:35.010 --> 00:33:36.020
Barb's driving.

569
00:33:36.100 --> 00:33:38.270
Why am I just hearing about this?

570
00:33:39.140 --> 00:33:40.190
I thought you knew.

571
00:33:40.270 --> 00:33:43.360
I told you. I don't want you
out after dark until Will is found.

572
00:33:43.440 --> 00:33:46.780
I know. I know. but it'd be
super weird if I'm not there.

573
00:33:46.860 --> 00:33:48.900
I mean. everyone's going.

574
00:33:48.990 --> 00:33:49.990
[sighs]

575
00:33:52.160 --> 00:33:54.080
Just... be back by 10:00.

576
00:33:55.490 --> 00:33:56.716
Why don't you take the boys. too?

577
00:33:56.740 --> 00:33:57.950
- No!
- Mmm-mmm.

578
00:33:59.620 --> 00:34:01.710
Don't you think you should be there?
For Will?

579
00:34:04.420 --> 00:34:05.670
- [gasps]
- [Holly groans]

580
00:34:05.750 --> 00:34:08.010
Sorry. Spasm.

581
00:34:11.880 --> 00:34:14.140
- [Holly whimpers]
- Oh...

582
00:34:14.220 --> 00:34:15.430
It's okay. Holly.

583
00:34:15.510 --> 00:34:17.350
- It's just a loud noise.
- Nice.

584
00:34:19.060 --> 00:34:21.350
- [sirens wailing]
- [people shouting] Will!

585
00:34:23.440 --> 00:34:26.650
[volunteer] Better come out. buddy.
Will. where are ya?

586
00:34:36.990 --> 00:34:39.870
[Callahan] Hey. you think
Earl really saw Will?

587
00:34:39.950 --> 00:34:42.920
I mean. what's he doin'
with a shaved head?

588
00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:44.580
And stealing food from Benny?

589
00:34:44.670 --> 00:34:47.340
Tell you what.
when we find him. we'll ask.

590
00:34:47.420 --> 00:34:49.050
Can't ask a corpse questions.

591
00:34:49.130 --> 00:34:50.920
- [whistle blowing]
- [volunteer 2] Hold up!

592
00:34:51.010 --> 00:34:52.470
You got something?

593
00:34:55.640 --> 00:34:57.760
- Hey. what do you got?
- [Mr. Clarke] Not sure.

594
00:34:57.850 --> 00:34:59.770
Maybe nothing.

595
00:34:59.850 --> 00:35:01.770
I found this. In there.

596
00:35:06.480 --> 00:35:08.650
[Powell] No way a kid
crawls through there.

597
00:35:09.690 --> 00:35:11.400
[Hopper] I don't know...

598
00:35:11.490 --> 00:35:12.860
a scared enough one might.

599
00:35:12.950 --> 00:35:15.320
His brother said he was good at hiding.

600
00:35:38.470 --> 00:35:40.430
[rhythmic beeping]

601
00:35:46.810 --> 00:35:48.480
[radio static]

602
00:35:51.440 --> 00:35:52.440
[Mike] El?

603
00:35:58.240 --> 00:36:01.200
No adults.
Just us and some meatloaf.

604
00:36:04.660 --> 00:36:07.790
Don't worry.
They won't tell anyone about you.

605
00:36:07.880 --> 00:36:10.290
They promise.
Right?

606
00:36:10.380 --> 00:36:12.920
We never would've upset you
if we knew you had superpowers.

607
00:36:14.260 --> 00:36:15.300
[Dustin] Ow!

608
00:36:15.380 --> 00:36:20.010
What Dustin is trying to say
is that they were just scared... earlier.

609
00:36:20.100 --> 00:36:21.140
That's all.

610
00:36:21.220 --> 00:36:23.140
We just wanted to find our friend.

611
00:36:23.720 --> 00:36:24.770
"Friend"?

612
00:36:24.850 --> 00:36:27.730
Yeah. friend.
Will?

613
00:36:27.810 --> 00:36:31.110
What is "friend"?

614
00:36:31.190 --> 00:36:32.610
Is she serious?

615
00:36:35.280 --> 00:36:36.700
Um. a friend...

616
00:36:36.780 --> 00:36:38.530
Is someone that you'd do anything for.

617
00:36:38.610 --> 00:36:41.740
You lend them your cool stuff.
like comic books and trading cards.

618
00:36:41.830 --> 00:36:43.120
And they never break a promise.

619
00:36:43.200 --> 00:36:45.120
- Especially when there's spit.
- Spit?

620
00:36:45.200 --> 00:36:48.960
A spit swear means...
[spits] you never break your word.

621
00:36:49.040 --> 00:36:50.460
It's a bond.

622
00:36:50.540 --> 00:36:54.210
That's super important. because friends...

623
00:36:54.300 --> 00:36:56.550
they tell each other things.

624
00:36:56.630 --> 00:36:58.380
Things that parents don't know.

625
00:37:01.470 --> 00:37:03.560
[music playing on car radio]

626
00:37:05.220 --> 00:37:07.270
[Nancy] Barbara. pull over.
[Barbara] What?

627
00:37:07.350 --> 00:37:08.640
Pull over!

628
00:37:11.360 --> 00:37:13.230
What are we doing here?

629
00:37:13.320 --> 00:37:14.900
His house is three blocks away.

630
00:37:14.980 --> 00:37:16.440
We can't park in the driveway.

631
00:37:16.530 --> 00:37:17.570
Are you serious?

632
00:37:17.650 --> 00:37:18.836
Yeah. the neighbors might see.

633
00:37:18.860 --> 00:37:21.570
This is so stupid.
I'm just gonna drop you off.

634
00:37:21.660 --> 00:37:23.490
Calm down. Barb.
Come on.

635
00:37:23.580 --> 00:37:26.120
You promised that you'd go.
You're coming.

636
00:37:26.200 --> 00:37:27.460
We're gonna have a great time.

637
00:37:27.540 --> 00:37:29.080
He just wants to get in your pants.

638
00:37:29.170 --> 00:37:30.790
[chuckling] No. he doesn't.

639
00:37:30.880 --> 00:37:33.170
Nance... seriously.

640
00:37:34.300 --> 00:37:36.340
He invited you to his house.

641
00:37:36.960 --> 00:37:38.340
His parents aren't home.

642
00:37:39.010 --> 00:37:40.680
Come on. you are not this stupid.

643
00:37:40.760 --> 00:37:42.760
Tommy H. and Carol are gonna be there.

644
00:37:42.850 --> 00:37:45.930
Tommy and Carol have been
having sex since. like. seventh grade.

645
00:37:46.930 --> 00:37:48.890
It'll probably just be. like. a big orgy.

646
00:37:48.980 --> 00:37:51.940
- Gross.
- I'm serious!

647
00:37:52.020 --> 00:37:53.310
All right. well...

648
00:37:54.320 --> 00:37:57.570
you can be. like. my guardian. All right?

649
00:37:57.650 --> 00:38:00.110
Make sure I don't get drunk
and do anything stupid.

650
00:38:00.200 --> 00:38:01.200
Ugh.

651
00:38:04.530 --> 00:38:05.740
Is that a new bra?

652
00:38:07.410 --> 00:38:08.540
No.

653
00:38:09.870 --> 00:38:11.830
[music playing in distance]

654
00:38:16.750 --> 00:38:18.460
[doorbell rings]

655
00:38:21.300 --> 00:38:22.970
Barb. chill.

656
00:38:23.890 --> 00:38:25.260
I'm chill.

657
00:38:30.350 --> 00:38:31.730
Hello. ladies.

658
00:38:44.700 --> 00:38:45.740
[grunts]

659
00:39:03.840 --> 00:39:05.300
[Sandra] What are you doing?

660
00:39:06.300 --> 00:39:07.810
It's freezing.

661
00:39:13.690 --> 00:39:15.060
You ever feel cursed?

662
00:39:18.520 --> 00:39:21.570
You know. the last person
to go missing here was in. uh...

663
00:39:23.360 --> 00:39:24.950
the summer of '23.

664
00:39:26.620 --> 00:39:28.910
The last suicide was the fall of '61.

665
00:39:34.210 --> 00:39:36.670
When'd the last person freeze to death?

666
00:39:40.170 --> 00:39:42.380
Hey. come back inside.

667
00:39:42.460 --> 00:39:44.470
Warm me up. Just...

668
00:39:47.090 --> 00:39:48.680
Just give me a minute out here.

669
00:39:51.390 --> 00:39:52.730
[Sandra sighs]

670
00:40:15.370 --> 00:40:17.120
[Lucas] What's the weirdo doing?

671
00:40:23.170 --> 00:40:24.210
El?

672
00:40:37.810 --> 00:40:38.900
Will.

673
00:40:39.560 --> 00:40:40.560
Superpowers.

674
00:40:47.700 --> 00:40:50.620
Did you see him?
On Mirkwood?

675
00:40:52.030 --> 00:40:53.240
Do you know where he is?

676
00:41:09.130 --> 00:41:10.840
[Mike] I don't understand.

677
00:41:11.760 --> 00:41:12.930
Hiding.

678
00:41:13.060 --> 00:41:14.680
Will is hiding?

679
00:41:19.440 --> 00:41:21.020
From the bad men?

680
00:41:23.940 --> 00:41:25.610
Then from who?

681
00:41:36.410 --> 00:41:37.410
[sighs]

682
00:42:23.380 --> 00:42:25.170
[camera shutter clicking]

683
00:42:29.260 --> 00:42:30.800
Where are you?

684
00:42:38.270 --> 00:42:39.600
[camera shutter clicking]

685
00:42:46.520 --> 00:42:47.780
[camera shutter clicking]

686
00:42:47.860 --> 00:42:49.030
- [woman screaming]
- [gasps]

687
00:42:51.280 --> 00:42:52.820
[panting]

688
00:42:52.910 --> 00:42:54.820
[screaming continues]

689
00:42:59.870 --> 00:43:02.160
- [Carol shrieking]
- [Tommy] One! Two!

690
00:43:02.250 --> 00:43:04.920
- Three!
- [Carol] Stop it. Tommy. no! Don't!

691
00:43:05.000 --> 00:43:07.670
- [Tommy laughing]
- You're such an asshole. Tommy.

692
00:43:07.750 --> 00:43:09.210
[rock music playing]

693
00:43:17.890 --> 00:43:18.890
[exhales]

694
00:43:22.890 --> 00:43:24.600
Is that supposed to impress me?

695
00:43:25.400 --> 00:43:28.480
- You're not?
- You are a cliché. you do realize that?

696
00:43:28.570 --> 00:43:29.610
You are a cliché.

697
00:43:29.690 --> 00:43:32.110
What with your...
your grades and your band practice.

698
00:43:32.190 --> 00:43:33.610
[laughing] I'm so not in band.

699
00:43:33.700 --> 00:43:36.620
Okay. party girl. Why don't you just. uh.
show us how it's done. then?

700
00:43:36.700 --> 00:43:37.700
Okay.

701
00:43:44.830 --> 00:43:46.806
- You gotta make a little hole right in...
- I got it.

702
00:43:46.830 --> 00:43:49.040
Yeah. she's smart. you douche!

703
00:43:53.670 --> 00:43:55.800
Chug. chug. chug.

704
00:43:55.880 --> 00:43:57.340
[all chanting] Chug. Chug. Chug.

705
00:44:04.270 --> 00:44:05.560
[Tommy whooping]

706
00:44:05.640 --> 00:44:06.850
[laughing]

707
00:44:09.900 --> 00:44:11.150
Barb. you wanna try?

708
00:44:11.980 --> 00:44:13.530
What? No.

709
00:44:13.610 --> 00:44:14.860
No. I don't want to. Thanks.

710
00:44:14.950 --> 00:44:16.070
- Come on.
- [Steve] Yeah...

711
00:44:16.160 --> 00:44:17.546
- Come on. Yeah.
- [Barbara] Nance. I don't want to.

712
00:44:17.570 --> 00:44:19.280
- It's fun! Just give it a...
- Nance...

713
00:44:19.370 --> 00:44:21.030
Just... Just give it a shot.

714
00:44:23.250 --> 00:44:24.290
Okay.

715
00:44:29.880 --> 00:44:31.000
So you just...

716
00:44:33.340 --> 00:44:34.760
[Tommy chuckles]

717
00:44:35.720 --> 00:44:37.760
- Gnarly.
- [Nancy] Are you okay?

718
00:44:37.840 --> 00:44:39.366
- [Barbara] Yeah.
- Barb. you're bleeding.

719
00:44:39.390 --> 00:44:41.350
I'm fine.
Where's your bathroom?

720
00:44:41.430 --> 00:44:44.020
Oh. it's... It's. uh. down past
the kitchen. to the left.

721
00:44:44.100 --> 00:44:45.680
[Barbara] Okay. Thanks.

722
00:44:45.770 --> 00:44:46.980
[camera shutter clicking]

723
00:44:48.650 --> 00:44:50.190
[chuckling] Oh.

724
00:44:56.030 --> 00:44:57.570
[screams]

725
00:44:59.070 --> 00:45:02.200
Oh. my. God!
What the hell. Tommy?

726
00:45:02.280 --> 00:45:03.290
No!

727
00:45:04.910 --> 00:45:06.830
- [shrieks]
- [Steve] Whoo!

728
00:45:06.910 --> 00:45:08.870
[Tommy laughing]

729
00:45:19.680 --> 00:45:21.180
[all laughing]

730
00:45:21.800 --> 00:45:26.060
[camera shutter clicking]

731
00:45:30.520 --> 00:45:32.360
[camera shutter clicking]

732
00:45:45.330 --> 00:45:46.370
[phone rings]

733
00:45:47.000 --> 00:45:48.040
Hello?

734
00:45:50.250 --> 00:45:52.830
- Hello.
- [muffled breathing on phone]

735
00:45:52.920 --> 00:45:54.750
Who is this?
[stammers]

736
00:45:57.840 --> 00:46:00.090
- [whimpers] Will?
- [muffled breathing continues]

737
00:46:01.550 --> 00:46:04.300
- [indistinct noise over phone]
- [sobbing] Will. it's me.

738
00:46:04.390 --> 00:46:06.140
Talk to me.

739
00:46:06.220 --> 00:46:07.600
I'm here.

740
00:46:07.680 --> 00:46:09.560
Just tell me where you are. honey.

741
00:46:09.640 --> 00:46:11.600
- I can hear you. Please.
- [static]

742
00:46:12.600 --> 00:46:14.270
- [Will distorted] <i>Mom?</i>
- [gasps]

743
00:46:14.360 --> 00:46:15.730
Will!

744
00:46:15.820 --> 00:46:19.440
[sobbing] Yes. it's me.
It's me.

745
00:46:19.530 --> 00:46:21.820
Where are you? Where are you?
Just talk to me...

746
00:46:21.910 --> 00:46:24.410
- [electricity spiking]
- [screams]

747
00:46:24.490 --> 00:46:25.530
Oh. no. no!

748
00:46:25.620 --> 00:46:26.660
No!

749
00:46:26.740 --> 00:46:28.250
No!

750
00:46:28.330 --> 00:46:31.040
[sobbing] Oh. no! No. no...

751
00:46:33.920 --> 00:46:35.210
No!

752
00:46:37.210 --> 00:46:38.920
[sobbing continues]

753
00:46:41.300 --> 00:46:43.180
[screams] No!

754
00:46:46.430 --> 00:46:48.640
[wailing]

755
00:46:52.060 --> 00:46:54.060
[whimpering]

756
00:46:59.690 --> 00:47:01.070
Jonathan?

757
00:47:03.700 --> 00:47:04.700
[softly] What...

758
00:47:14.170 --> 00:47:15.790
- [music blares]
- [gasps]

759
00:47:15.880 --> 00:47:17.880
["Should I Stay or Should I Go"
playing on stereo]

760
00:47:19.760 --> 00:47:20.920
[whimpers]

761
00:47:22.090 --> 00:47:24.340
[music continues]

762
00:47:36.400 --> 00:47:37.440
[whispers] Will...

763
00:47:37.520 --> 00:47:39.570
[music continues]

764
00:47:48.160 --> 00:47:49.530
[electricity crackling]

765
00:47:49.620 --> 00:47:51.200
Will...

766
00:47:52.330 --> 00:47:54.000
[sobs] Will. is that you?

767
00:47:59.420 --> 00:48:00.500
[music stops]

768
00:48:01.460 --> 00:48:02.460
[whimpers]

769
00:48:07.970 --> 00:48:09.220
[screaming]

770
00:48:09.300 --> 00:48:10.640
[growling]

771
00:48:17.270 --> 00:48:18.650
[breathlessly] Oh. my God.

772
00:48:21.360 --> 00:48:22.940
[whimpering] Oh. God...

773
00:48:25.900 --> 00:48:28.030
Oh. my God...

774
00:48:28.120 --> 00:48:29.490
[engine starts]

775
00:48:29.570 --> 00:48:31.740
[music resumes playing]

776
00:48:31.830 --> 00:48:34.120
[electricity crackling]

777
00:48:43.460 --> 00:48:45.800
[music continues]

778
00:48:53.270 --> 00:48:54.850
[music continues]

779
00:49:12.240 --> 00:49:14.120
- [Tommy shudders]
- [Carol] I'm freezing.

780
00:49:14.200 --> 00:49:18.500
Hmm... well. I hear his
mom's room has a fireplace.

781
00:49:18.580 --> 00:49:19.896
[Steve] Are you kidding?
[Carol] Oh. yeah?

782
00:49:19.920 --> 00:49:22.250
Okay. well. you know.
you are cleaning the sheets.

783
00:49:22.340 --> 00:49:23.590
- You all right?
- Yeah.

784
00:49:23.670 --> 00:49:26.340
Yeah?
Come on. let's get you some dry clothes.

785
00:49:26.420 --> 00:49:27.590
[sighs]

786
00:49:31.890 --> 00:49:33.180
[Barbara] Nance!

787
00:49:33.310 --> 00:49:34.600
Nancy.

788
00:49:35.560 --> 00:49:37.310
Where are you going?

789
00:49:37.390 --> 00:49:38.440
Nowhere.

790
00:49:38.520 --> 00:49:40.350
Just... upstairs.

791
00:49:40.440 --> 00:49:42.060
To change.

792
00:49:42.150 --> 00:49:44.900
I... fell in the pool. [chuckles]

793
00:49:47.650 --> 00:49:49.530
Why don't you go ahead and go home.

794
00:49:49.610 --> 00:49:51.990
I'll just... I'll get a ride or something.

795
00:49:52.070 --> 00:49:53.450
Nance...

796
00:49:54.200 --> 00:49:55.910
Barb...

797
00:49:55.990 --> 00:49:57.580
I'm fine.

798
00:49:57.660 --> 00:50:00.080
This isn't you.

799
00:50:01.210 --> 00:50:02.830
I'm fine.

800
00:50:02.920 --> 00:50:06.500
Just... go ahead and go home. okay?

801
00:50:11.430 --> 00:50:12.470
[scoffs]

802
00:50:18.480 --> 00:50:19.520
[camera shutter clicks]

803
00:50:26.400 --> 00:50:27.650
Thanks.

804
00:50:30.570 --> 00:50:32.360
[inhales]

805
00:50:32.450 --> 00:50:33.990
Um...

806
00:50:34.070 --> 00:50:35.700
some privacy. maybe?

807
00:50:35.780 --> 00:50:37.290
[clicks tongue] Oh...

808
00:50:37.370 --> 00:50:39.000
Yeah. right.
Sorry. [chuckles]

809
00:50:43.750 --> 00:50:44.790
Steve?

810
00:50:58.810 --> 00:50:59.980
Damn.

811
00:51:00.100 --> 00:51:01.180
[chuckles]

812
00:51:02.310 --> 00:51:03.560
Shut up.

813
00:51:29.420 --> 00:51:33.680
[camera shutter clicking]

814
00:51:34.590 --> 00:51:36.140
[shutter jamming]

815
00:51:36.220 --> 00:51:38.180
[whirring]

816
00:52:08.750 --> 00:52:10.420
[electricity pulsating]

817
00:52:12.010 --> 00:52:13.380
[growls]

818
00:52:13.470 --> 00:52:15.090
- [roars]
- [Barbara shrieks]

819
